# ğŸ“Œ 590. N-ary Tree Postorder Traversal
ğŸ”— https://leetcode.com/problems/n-ary-tree-postorder-traversal/

---

## ğŸ§  Concept
Postorder traversal visits all children first and processes the current node at the end.

---

## ğŸŒ³ Data Structure
N-ary Tree (each node contains a list of children)

---

## ğŸ“ Traversal Pattern


---

## ğŸš€ Algorithm (Iterative using Stack)

1. If root is null â†’ return empty list  
2. Push root into stack  
3. While stack is not empty:
   - Pop node  
   - Add its value to result  
   - Push its children (left to right)  
4. Reverse the result list  

---

## ğŸ’» Pseudocode

```text
push root

while stack not empty:
    node = pop
    add node value

    for each child:
        push child

reverse result

CODE

RECURSIVE

class Solution {
    public List<Integer> preorder(Node root) {
        List<Integer> list=new ArrayList<>();
        preOrder(root,list);

        return list;
    }
    private static void preOrder(Node root,List<Integer> list){
        if(root==null){
            return;
        }
        list.add(root.val);
        for(int i=0;i<root.children.size();i++){
            preOrder(root.children.get(i),list);
        }
    }
}

ITERATIVE
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> preorder(Node root) {
        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        if (root == null) return result;

        Stack<Node> stack = new Stack<>();
        stack.push(root);

        while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
            Node curr = stack.pop();
            result.add(curr.val);

            // Push children in reverse order
            for (int i = curr.children.size() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
                stack.push(curr.children.get(i));
            }
        }

        return result;
    }
}
